Description: Flat and circular small corroded copper alloy disc, possibly the head of a nail or stud; a shallow groove is visible around the edge.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, Probably from the surrounding area towards Tell Belim.
Curator's comments: One of the bronze "flat, round" "nail-heads" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.80, p.186, pl.28)
